closed_at":"2020-11-17T02:35:14Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":"resolved","sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"# Problem\r\nSorry if this is not an issue in this repository.\r\n\r\nsandbox\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/react-hook-form-with-yup-forked-1ihqf?file=/src/index.js\r\n\r\nI use yup's schema validation.\r\nThe schema is nested as follows.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst schema = yup.object().shape({\r\n  user: yup.object().shape({\r\n    firstName: yup.string().required(),\r\n    lastName: yup.string().required(),\r\n    age: yup.string().required()\r\n  })\r\n```\r\n\r\nI want the initial render to be in an error state, so I run trigger in useEffect.\r\nAnd The mode of validation is onBlur.\r\n\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  // initial validate\r\n  React.useEffect(() => {\r\n    trigger();\r\n  }, [trigger]);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe initial render shows the error as expected, but when I finish entering the first item, the error disappears even though there are items that have not been entered.\r\n\r\n![screencast 2020-11-16 21-40-23](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8813191/99254231-5cd92d00-2855-11eb-8b1a-148e1e2bfe3c.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\nWithout nesting the schema, it behaved as expected.\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"bluebill1049","id":10513364,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwNTEzMzY0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10513364?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bluebill1049","html_url":"https://github.com/bluebill1049","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bluebill1049/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bluebill1049/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bluebill1049/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bluebill1049/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bluebill104